你被盖思秒杀了
Yeah, you've been Garthed.

61
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:14,360
听着  你追踪我们就够糟的了
Look, it's bad enough that you're tracking us,

62
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,500
你居然还说什么
but it's even worse

63
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,800
我们被盖思秒杀了
when you say we've been "Garthed."

64
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,330
是啊
Yeah.

65
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:23,340
好吧  我们得关掉手机GPS
Okay, we got to lose the gps on our phones

66
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,970
因为盖思一直在追踪我们
because garth has been tracking us,

67
00:03:24,970 --> 00:03:27,970
显然其他猎人也是  方便他分配任务
and other hunters, apparently, to assign cases.

68
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:30,110
挺效率啊
Smart.

69
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:31,610
鲍比也会这样
A total Bobby move.

70
00:03:31,610 --> 00:03:33,780
怎么回事
What's the deal?

71
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:37,280
挺近的  密歇根  法明顿山
Uh, well, it's close -- Farmington Hills, Michigan.

72
00:03:37,290 --> 00:03:39,950
有人在上锁的公寓里惨遭车裂
Dude got ripped limb from limb inside his locked apartment.

73
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:41,320
不是好事
That's not good.

74
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,620
猎魔
Working a case.

75
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,990
等着凯文消息的期间
As long as we're waiting on Kevin,

76
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:47,430
就把这当乐子吧
that'll be our fun.

77
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,700
警长
Sheriff.

78
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:57,140
我是塔戈特特工
Special agent Taggart.

79
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:59,270
这是我搭档罗斯伍德特工
This is my partner, special agent Rosewood.

80
00:03:59,270 --> 00:04:01,610
联调局  你们挺迅速啊
FBI? You guys are quick.

81
00:04:01,610 --> 00:04:03,010
尸体都没搬走呢
Haven't even got the body out yet.

82
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:06,580
联调局都是工作狂  不休息的
Well, the FBI is all work, no play.

83
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,070
这样吧  你跟我说下情况
You know, why don't you give me the tour

84
00:04:08,070 --> 00:04:09,180
我搭档到处看看
while my partner looks around?

85
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,680
我自己干效率比较高
I work better on my own.

86
00:04:10,690 --> 00:04:14,720
你们说了算  跟我来
Your world, agent. Follow me.

87
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:25,330
死者叫艾德・尼尔森  31岁
Vic's name was Ed Nelson, 31 years old,

88
00:04:25,330 --> 00:04:27,530
保险核保人
an insurance-claim adjuster.

89
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:30,370
独居  这不奇怪
He lived alone, which was a real shocker,

90
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:32,510
这儿到处是玩具
considering his place is full of toys.

91
00:04:32,510 --> 00:04:35,610
怎么回事
So what happened?

92
00:04:35,610 --> 00:04:37,210
没有强行闯入的迹象
No sign of forced entry.

93
00:04:37,210 --> 00:04:41,350
目前看来  他是被人绑起来  扯碎了
Near as we can tell, he was tied up and pulled apart.

94
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:43,680
不是吓死的就是流血致死
Died of the shock or massive blood loss.

95
00:04:43,690 --> 00:04:45,220
这看他自己了
Dealer's choice on that one.

96
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:47,690
这些链条是怎么回事
So what about these chains?

97
00:04:47,690 --> 00:04:49,190
那是锁子甲
That's actually chain mail.

98
00:04:49,190 --> 00:04:52,030
不是吧
Seriously?

99
00:04:52,030 --> 00:04:56,130
他手腕和脚踝上都有清晰的绳印
We did find clear rope-burn marks on his wrists and ankles.

100
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:10,610
那么
So, anything...

101
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:12,280
他身上有什么不见了吗
Missing from the body?

102
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,980
你是说除了胳膊腿吗
You mean aside from the arms and legs?

103
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:19,050
没有
Uh... nope.

104
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:20,850
都在呢  肠子肚子都在
All there -- twig and berries, too.

105
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:24,020
邻居有听到什么奇怪的声音吗
What about the neighbors? Did they hear anything weird?

106
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,190
楼下的邻居说
Uh, neighbor downstairs said

107
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:27,260
她半夜被惊醒
she got woke up in the middle of the night

108
00:05:27,260 --> 00:05:29,030
因为听到马声
by the sound of horses

109
00:05:29,030 --> 00:05:30,530
又是跺蹄子又是飞奔
stomping their feet and galloping.

110
00:05:30,530 --> 00:05:34,200
我们没看到蹄印
We didn't find any hoofprints.

111
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:37,570
她听到的大概是电视  要么就是做恶梦
She probably heard a tv or was having a bad dream

112
00:05:37,570 --> 00:05:39,340
她嗑药磕大了
or she was high as balls.

113
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:43,310
幸好  他手机上有条不错的线索
Fortunately, we got a real lead off his cellphone.

114
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:45,310
电话记录显示
According to the phone records,

115
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:49,580
艾德最后一通电话是跟兰斯・雅各布森
Ed's last call was from a guy called Lance Jacobsen,

116
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:54,120
一个会计  也是三十多  也是独居
an accountant, also 30s, also lives alone.

117
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,060
为什么说是线索
How's he a lead?

118
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:58,630
他们两人大概谈了15分钟
The two of them talked together for 15 minutes,

119
00:05:58,630 --> 00:06:02,730
然后兰斯给艾德发了些怒气冲冲的短信
and then Lance sent Ed here all kinds of angry texts.

120
00:06:02,730 --> 00:06:04,870
一些是一般的狠话
Some of them were your typical threat stuff,

121
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:06,970
也有些挺怪的
but some were a little weird.

122
00:06:06,970 --> 00:06:08,600
怎么个怪法
Weird how?

123
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,800
比如
Like, uh...

124
00:06:10,810 --> 00:06:13,540
你对我们的罪行要血债血偿
"You shall bleed for your crimes against us,"

125
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,980
后面是一个骷髅的表情
followed by the emoticon of a skull.

126
00:06:15,980 --> 00:06:17,510
还有这个
And this beauty --

127
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:21,780
我是个法师  我会灭了你
"I am a mage. I will destroy you."

128
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:25,450
现在这些孩子  都在闹哪样啊
These kids today with their texting and murder.

129
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:29,790
我的人把兰斯带去局里问话了
My men just brought Lance into the station for questioning.

130
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:32,460
我们要先审他一下
Well, we're gonna need to take first crack at the suspect.

131
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:35,460
我说了  你们说了算
Like I said, agent, it's your world.

132
00:06:40,470 --> 00:06:44,800
兰斯・雅各布森  我们是联调局的
Lance Jacobsen? We're with the FBI.

133
00:06:44,810 --> 00:06:46,840
联调局
The FBI?

134
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:50,180
真不敢相信
I can't believe this is happening.

135
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:52,680
艾德居然死了
I can't believe Ed's dead.

136
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:56,420
兰斯
Lance?

137
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:58,250
兰斯  呼吸
Lance, just -- just breathe.

138
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,450
呼吸  没事的
Just breathe. You're fine.

139
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:03,820
我们得问你几个问题
We just need to ask you a few questions.

140
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:04,820
冷静一点
Try to calm down.

141
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:07,460
我们想问你
We want to know about the, uh --

142
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:10,500
你昨晚发给艾德的那些短信
the texts you sent Ed last night.

143
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:13,270
他们带我来的时候我就说了那些不是我发的
I told them when they brought me in those texts weren't from me.

144
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:15,770
但是你的手机和艾德的手机里都有记录
Well, your phone and Ed's phone say otherwise.

145
00:07:15,770 --> 00:07:18,200
我是说是我发的  但不是我发的
No, I mean, they were from me, but they weren't from me me.

146
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:24,010
你真觉得这么说就清楚了
Did you really think that sentence was gonna clear things up?

147
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:26,950
对不起
I'm sorry.

148
00:07:26,950 --> 00:07:28,620
这都是误会
This is all a big misunderstanding.

149
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:32,050
那些短信是以法师灰狐狸这个身份
Those text messages were from Greyfox the Mystic

150
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:33,990
发给贫士撒格瑞姆
to Thargrim the Difficult.

151
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:37,620
那是我们在月门里的角色
Our characters in Moondoor.

152
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:40,990
月门是我和艾德玩的游戏
Moondoor is a game that Ed and I play.

153
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,030
我们玩真人扮演游戏
We're LARPers. Live-action role-playing?

154
00:07:44,030 --> 00:07:48,070
是啊  真人扮演  是有意思
Right. Larping. Good times.

155
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:50,340
我们每隔一个周末在民俗公园玩月门
We play Moondoor every other weekend at Heritage Park.

156
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:52,270
一切信息都在我们网站上
All the info about it is on our website.

157
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:53,670
你们还有网站呢
You guys have a website.

158
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,710
是啊  一个玩家设计的
Yeah, one of the players designed it.

159
00:07:55,710 --> 00:07:57,340
事实上  如果你登陆网站
In fact, if you log onto the site,

160
00:07:57,350 --> 00:07:59,380
他们应该发布了昨晚集会的照片
they should have posted pictures from last night's feast.

161
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:00,750
我整晚都在那儿
I was there all night.

162
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,920
这些跟你发的短信有什么关系
What does any of this have to do with the texts?

163
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:06,520
我在游戏中的角色是法师灰狐狸
I play a character named Greyfox the Mystic.

164
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:10,390
我是游戏里一个法力极强的法师
I'm a very, very powerful mage in the game.

165
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:17,000
法力极强  继续
Okay, uh, very powerful. Go on.

166
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,800
艾德是
Ed is...

167
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:24,470
艾德是老森林的撒格瑞姆 贫士
Ed was Thargrim the Difficult of the Elder Forest,

168
00:08:24,470 --> 00:08:27,740
哈格里姆和布尔芬的儿子  兄弟是
son of Hargrim and Bouphin, brother to --

169
00:08:31,380 --> 00:08:33,750
我是梅林他就是兰斯洛特
He was Lancelot to my Merlin.

170
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:38,720
你们既然这么铁  怎么发短信威胁他
Well, if you guys were so tight, then why the threatening messages?

171
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:40,720
我们被授予女王荣誉护卫一职
We were named to the queen's honor guard

172
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:43,120
是为这周末的诸国之战做准备
in anticipation of the coming battle of kingdoms this weekend.

173
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:44,890
我觉得他破坏了规矩
I thought he broke protocol,

174
00:08:44,890 --> 00:08:48,230
所以结束后我打电话给他  说他作弊
so I called Ed after game hours and accused him of cheating,

175
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,560
我提出跟他决斗
and then I challenged him to a duel.

176
00:08:50,570 --> 00:08:53,230
-决斗  -天明时分剑锋对魔杖
- A duel? - Wands and swords at dawn.

177
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:59,270
魔杖是指有魔法的手杖吗
Now, when you say "wands"" do you mean magic wands?

178
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:02,480
没有魔法  特工
No. Un-magic wands, agent.

179
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:05,810
因为我就想带着没魔法的去决斗呢
Because what I really want in a duel is an un-magic wand.

180
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:10,750
就是假魔杖  这叫游戏
Yes! Fake wands! It's a game!

181
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:13,590
真不敢相信
I can't believe it.

182
00:09:13,590 --> 00:09:15,420
诸神啊
Oh, ye gods!

183
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:19,130
撒格瑞姆 贫士陨落啦
Thargrim the Difficult has fallen!

184
